  "prompt": "Were humans around during the existence of dinosaur?",
  "response": "No, humans were not around during the time of the dinosaurs. Dinosaurs existed during the Mesozoic Era, which lasted from about 252 to 66 million years ago. The most well-known period of dinosaur dominance was the Late Cretaceous, which ended with a mass extinction event approximately 66 million years ago. \n\nIn contrast, anatomically modern humans (Homo sapiens) appeared only about 300,000 years ago. There is a vast time gap between the extinction of the last dinosaurs and the emergence of humans, so they never coexisted.",
